<plot>POISON WIND tells the story of a corrupt government, unconscionable greed and a policy of destruction aimed at the Aboriginal Homelands of Indigenous People from the 1940's until today. It is a documentary set against the Grand Canyon and Indigenous landscape of the Desert Southwest. This film focuses on the lives being destroyed by the horror of uranium mining and effects of radiation...as a government's cruel secret is carried on the face of the wind.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?437236</url></doc>
